\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is a non zero vector, thus, there are no stationery points, and the optimum
 points are not interior points.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\lang english
Let's check on the boundary, we need to solve:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{x\in R^{n}}/\min\left\{ a^{T}x:\left\Vert x\right\Vert _{2}=\alpha\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\lang english
using the Cauchy-Schwartz Inequality:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left|a^{T}x\right|\leq\left\Vert a\right\Vert _{2}\left\Vert x\right\Vert _{2}=\alpha\left\Vert a\right\Vert _{2}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
